The paper deals with Bayesian agents learning to predict the policies of other agents in a multi-agent environment, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the convergence of agents based on Thompson sampling, which is a technique used in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely to be relevant to this paper.
